It is mutinous for police operatives to down tools, the Commissioner (CP) in charge of the Railway Command, Mrs. Yetunde Longe, said yesterday. Her warning came in the wake of the rumoured strike action being planned by the rank and file of the police. The police chief gave the admonition during a lecture at the command’s headquarters in Lagos She warned those under her Command to perish the idea of going on strike to press home their agitations, urging them to remain disciplined and selfless in the service to the country. There were reports that the rank and file of the police planned to commence a nation-wide strike action on March 26 to protest condition of service.   Buhari, governors agree on Adamu as consensus chair     Buhari hosts APC Chairmanship aspirants to dinner     2023: Bode George, Oladipo, 35 others to determine PDP…   Although the police high command have not officially reacted to the purported planned strike, Inspector-General (IG) Alkali Usman had since last week sent messages across to assure the aggrieved personnel that their concerns were bring addressed. Advising those under her command, CP Longe said any act that would further damage the reputation of the police would not be tolerated. She also informed them about IG’s efforts on the immediate computation of salaries under the new structure, tax reliefs for police operatives, among other welfare packages. She urged them to be alive to their responsibilities because any act of disloyalty from them could embolden criminals who vandalise railway assets.